se%20of%20force%20against%20members%20of%20Congress%20nearly%20doubled%20from%20January%20to%20June%20of%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20a%20recent%20study%20shared%20with%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20published%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago's%20Project%20on%20Security%20and%20Threats%20(CPOST)%2C%20found%20that%20as%20of%20June%2026%2C%2017%25%20of%20the%20American%20public%20%E2%80%94%20an%20estimated%2044%20million%20people%20%E2%80%94%20supported%20using%20violence%20to%20coerce%20lawmakers.%20That's%20up%20from%209%25%20when%20the%20survey%20was%20conducted%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spike%20was%20most%20pronounced%20among%20self-identified%20Democrats%3A%20in%20January%2C%207%25%20of%20Democrats%20supported%20using%20political%20violence%20against%20lawmakers%2C%20and%20that%20number%20climbed%20to%2016%25%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20contrast%2C%20the%20support%20for%20political%20violence%20against%20Congress%20among%20self-identifying%20Republicans%20increased%20by%2050%25.%20Overall%2C%20a%20higher%20percentage%20of%20these%20Republicans%20%E2%80%94%2018%25%20of%20all%20respondents%20%E2%80%94%20endorse%20the%20use%20of%20force%20against%20lawmakers%20compared%20to%20Democrats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20say%20violence%20or%20coercion%2C%20we're%20using%20'use%20of%20force'%20specifically%20because%20we%20know%20the%20respondents%20interpret%20that%20as%20meaning%2C%20'even%20if%20some%20people%20are%20injured%20and%20killed%2C'%26quot%3B%20Robert%20Pape%2C%20a%20political%20science%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%20and%20the%20study's%20author%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20while%20support%20for%20violence%20against%20members%20of%20Congress%20increased%20%26quot%3Bacross%20the%20political%20spectrum%2C%20the%20rise%20was%20sharpest%20among%20Democrats%2C%20where%20it%20grew%20by%20about%202.5%20times.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20did%20not%20draw%20a%20specific%20causal%20link%20for%20the%20rise%20in%20support%20for%20extremism%20among%20Democrats%2C%20but%20noted%20that%20it%20coincides%20with%20%26quot%3Bgrowing%20anger%20over%20the%20Republican-controlled%20House%20of%20Representatives%20and%20hearings%20that%20they%20have%20held%20painting%20a%20disparaging%20picture%20of%20Democrats.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPape's%20report%2C%20which%20was%20published%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20also%20clocked%20a%20significant%20jump%20over%20the%20last%20several%20months%20in%20public%20support%20for%20using%20violence%20to%20restore%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecifically%2C%20the%20survey%20found%20roughly%204%25%20of%20Americans%20%E2%80%94%20an%20estimated%2012%20million%20people%20%E2%80%94%20supported%20using%20violence%20to%20return%20Trump%20to%20office%20in%20April.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20June%2C%20that%20number%20spiked%20to%20an%20estimated%2018%20million%20Americans%2C%20about%20a%2050%25%20increase.%20The%20CPOST%20survey%20polled%203%2C543%20adults%20between%20June%2022%20and%20June%2026%20had%20a%202.3%25%20margin%20of%20error.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPape%20also%20noted%20that%20rise%20in%20radical%20support%20for%20violence%20across%20the%20aisle%20is%20connected%20to%20%26quot%3Bperceived%20corruption%20in%20our%20democratic%20institutions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20credible%20evidence%20that%20the%20more%20there's%20distrust%20in%20democracy%2C%20the%20more%20that's%20leading%20to%20radical%20support%20for%20the%20use%20of%20force%20for%20both%20conservative%2C%20Republican%20causes%20and%20also%20for%20liberal%20causes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpublic-support-violence-coerce-congress-doubled-over-6-months-study-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690323182000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F647e14dba52c4b001936a375%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpublic-support-violence-coerce-congress-doubled-over-6-months-study-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BThe%20more%20there's%20distrust%20in%20democracy%2C%20the%20more%20that's%20leading%20to%20radical%20support%20for%20the%20use%20of%20force%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study's%20author%20told%20Insider.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ssheth%40businessinsider.com%20(Sonam%20Sheth)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpublic-support-violence-coerce-congress-doubled-over-6-months-study-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20it%20was%20like%20to%20live%20at%20the%20Los%20Alamos%20lab%20site%20during%20the%20Manhattan%20Project%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222213%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Buildings%20around%20Ashley%20Pond%20at%20the%20Los%20Alamos%20Project%20Y%20Site%20in%201942%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c02bc6ed4f4600196389c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221659%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Los%20Alamos%20Ranch%20School%20buildings%20in%201942%2C%20which%20became%20part%20of%20the%20Los%20Alamos%20Project%20Y%20site.%3Cp%3ENational%20Security%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%201943%2C%20hundreds%20of%20people%20converged%20on%20a%20desert%20in%20New%20Mexico%20to%20work%20on%20the%20Manhattan%20Project.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBuilding%20the%20atomic%20bomb%20required%20a%20furious%20working%20pace%20and%20the%20utmost%20secrecy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20also%20forever%20changed%20the%20landscape%20of%20Los%20Alamos%20and%20the%20lives%20of%20its%20residents.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Los%20Alamos%20was%20just%20one%20of%20many%20sites%20dedicated%20to%20the%20Manhattan%20Project%2C%20it%20was%20the%20most%20remote%2C%20and%20the%20most%20secret.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELocated%20in%20the%20desert%2C%20it%20has%20mountain%20views%20and%20vivid%20sunsets.%20It's%20where%20scientists%20prepared%20the%20bomb%20for%20the%20Trinity%20Test.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20J.%20Robert%20Oppenheimer%20thought%20he'd%20only%20need%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.aip.org%2Faapt%2Fajp%2Farticle%2F88%2F12%2F1175%2F859737%2FManhattan-Project-The-Story-of-the-Century-Bruce%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20few%20dozen%3C%2Fa%3E%20scientists%20to%20complete%20the%20job.%20The%20number%20quickly%20rose%2C%20and%20Los%20Alamos%20became%20a%20boom%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%201945%2C%20the%20population%20had%20grown%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.osti.gov%2Fincludes%2Fopennet%2Fincludes%2FMED_scans%2FBook%2520VIII%2520-%2520%2520Volume%25201%2520-%2520Los%2520Alamos%2520Project%2520(Y)%2520-%2520General.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%208%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20included%20military%20personnel%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com.gi%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DBWek8zJ-U7IC%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%26rview%3D1%26source%3Dgbs_vpt_read%23v%3Donepage%26q%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eengineers%2C%20technicians%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20scientists'%20families.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeading%20it%20all%20was%20Oppenheimer%2C%20an%20enigmatic%20figure%20who%20inspired%20loyalty%20but%20was%20difficult%20to%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhysicist%20Abraham%20Pais%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FJ_Robert_Oppenheimer%2FEoA8DwAAQBAJ%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D1%26dq%3D%2522In%2Ball%2Bmy%2Blife%2BI%2Bhave%2Bnever%2Bknown%2Ba%2Bpersonality%2Bmore%2Bcomplex%2Bthan%2BRobert%2BOppenheimer%2C%25E2%2580%259D%26pg%3DPA139%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BIn%20all%20my%20life%20I%20have%20never%20known%20a%20personality%20more%20complex%20than%20Robert%20Oppenheimer%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20may%20explain%2C%20he%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhy%20different%20people%20reacted%20to%20him%20in%20such%20extremely%20varied%20ways.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20loved%20him.%20Some%20loathed%20him.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20personally%20recruited%20a%20number%20of%20scientists%20to%20come%20to%20Los%20Alamos%2C%20which%20was%20known%20as%20Project%20Y.%20It%20wasn't%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20notion%20of%20disappearing%20into%20the%20New%20Mexico%20desert%20for%20an%20indeterminate%20period%20and%20under%20quasi-military%20auspices%20disturbed%20a%20good%20many%20scientists%20and%20the%20families%20of%20many%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20Oppenheimer%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DHw4AAAAAMBAJ%26pg%3DPA181%26dq%3D%2522This%2Bjob%2C%2Bif%2Bit%2Bwere%2Bachieved%2C%2Bwould%2Bbe%2Ba%2Bpart%2Bof%2Bhistory.%2522%26hl%3Den%26sa%3DX%26ved%3D2ahUKEwi3ja_MxZaAAxUZGjQIHZ8fB0QQ6AF6BAgMEAI%23v%3Donepage%26q%3D%2522This%2520job%252C%2520if%2520it%2520were%2520achieved%252C%2520would%2520be%2520a%2520part%2520of%2520history.%2522%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elater%20wrote%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20he%20said%2C%20they%20knew%20that%20their%20work%20could%20determine%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20war%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Bthis%20job%2C%20if%20it%20were%20achieved%2C%20would%20be%20a%20part%20of%20history.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20two%20dozen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmanhattan-project-scientists-who-won-nobel-prizes-2023-7%5C%22%3ENobel%20Prize%20winners%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20current%20and%20future%2C%20contributed%20to%20the%20Manhattan%20Project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20were%20also%20local%20people%20who%20worked%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%