f%20the%20Los%20Alamos%20National%20Laboratory%20in%201998.%3Cp%3ELos%20Alamos%20National%20Laboratory%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESituated%207%2C300%20feet%20above%20sea%20level%20and%20roughly%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flosalamos.unm.edu%2Fcommunity%2Fabout-los-alamos.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E35%20miles%20from%20Santa%20Fe%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Los%20Alamos%20site%20seemed%20ideal%20for%20a%20secret%20laboratory.%20In%20addition%20to%20being%20isolated%2C%20the%20school%20was%20difficult%20to%20reach%2C%20accessible%20only%20by%20a%20twisty%20gravel%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20was%20plenty%20of%20space%20and%20weather%20suitable%20for%20year-round%20construction.%20Thus%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiopscience.iop.org%2Fbook%2Fmono%2F978-1-6817-4605-0%2Fchapter%2Fbk978-1-6817-4605-0ch5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emet%20the%20criteria%3C%2Fa%3E%20stipulated%20by%20Gen.%20Leslie%20Groves%2C%20the%20project's%20director.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fahf.nuclearmuseum.org%2Fahf%2Fhistory%2Fcivilian-displacement-los-alamos-nm%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egovernment%20paid%3C%2Fa%3E%20%24424%2C971%20for%20the%20Los%20Alamos%20Ranch%20School%20and%20nearly%2050%2C000%20acres%20of%20surrounding%20land.%20It%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nps.gov%2Farticles%2F000%2Fhispanic-homesteaders-and-the-los-alamos-national-laboratory.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealso%20displaced%3C%2Fa%3E%2032%20homesteaders%20in%20the%20surrounding%20areas%20who%20were%20paid%20far%20less%20for%20their%20land.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EConstant%20construction%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECompared%20to%20the%20Chicago%20labs%2C%20where%20some%20of%20the%20work%20on%20the%20Manhattan%20Project%20was%20being%20done%2C%20Los%20Alamos%20was%20starting