nstruction%20was%20nearly%20constant%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20influx%20of%20people.%20Trucks%20rumbled%20down%20the%20roads%2C%20and%20building%20materials%20lay%20heaped%20in%20piles%20around%20the%20site%2C%20Laura%20Fermi%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.uchicago.edu%2Fucp%2Fbooks%2Fbook%2Fchicago%2FA%2Fbo3628811.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20recalled%20how%20easy%20it%20was%20to%20get%20lost%20because%20all%20the%20buildings%20looked%20alike%2C%20painted%20the%20same%20green%2C%20and%20there%20were%20no%20street%20names.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20the%20Manhattan%20Project%2C%20workers%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.aip.org%2Faapt%2Fajp%2Farticle%2F88%2F12%2F1175%2F859737%2FManhattan-Project-The-Story-of-the-Century-Bruce%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewould%20construct%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20600%20housing%20units%2C%20including%20dozens%20of%20dormitories%20and%20barracks%20for%20unmarried%20personnel%20and%20the%20military.%20There%20were%20also%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fahf.nuclearmuseum.org%2Fvoices%2Foral-histories%2Fanna-mae-gillespies-interview%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edorms%20for%20married%20couples%3C%2Fa%3E%20whose%20jobs%20weren't%20as%20well-paid%20as%20the%20scientists'.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20coveted%20houses%20were%20originally%20part%20of%20the%20school.%20They%20came%20to%20be%20nicknamed%20%26quot%3BBathtub%20Row%26quot%3B%20because%20the%20newer%20houses%20only%20had%20showers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20attractive%2C%20well-built%20cottages%2C%20far%20more%20desirable%20than%20any%20later%20building%2C%26quot%3B%20Laura%20Fermi%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20homes'%20residents%2C%20including%20Oppenheimer%2C%20lent%20a%20certain%20cach%C3%A9%20to%20the%20area%2C%20too.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECreating%20a%20small%20city%20required%20more%20than%20just%20housing.%20Schools%2C%20courts%2C%20stores%2C%20a%20post%20office%2C%20a%20fire%20department%2C%20and%20a%20hospital%20all%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.aip.org%2Faapt%2Fajp%2Farticle%2F88%2F12%2F1175%2F859737%2FManhattan-Project-The-Story-of-the-Century-Bruce%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeventually%20appeared%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Los%20Alamos%20also%20needed%20veterinarians%20for%20the%20Military%20Police's%20horses%2C%20dentists%2C%20doctors%2C%20and%20garbage%20collectors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3BTechnical%20Area%26quot%3B%20was%20a%20top-secret%20space%20that%20required%20workers%20to%20show%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FAtomic_Spaces%2Fr7zvAAAAMAAJ%3Fhl%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Especial%20badge%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F25637414%3Fmag%3Dlos-alamos-secret-library%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eguard%20house%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Administrative%20buildings%2C%20labs%2C%20and%20warehouses%20clustered%20around%20a%20pond%20where%20the%20school's%20students%20used%20to%20ice%20skate.%20All%20were%20sequestered%20behind%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.osti.gov%2Fopennet%2Fmanhattan-project-history%2FPlaces%2FLosAlamos%2Ftech-area.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echain-link%20fence%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhysicist%20McAllister%20Hull%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FRider_of_the_Pale_Horse%2FddOhAwAAQBAJ%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D1%26dq%3D%2522los%2Balamos%2522%2B%2522fences%2Bwithin%2Bfences%2522%26pg%3DPA26%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edescribed%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%26quot%3Bfences%20within%20fences%26quot%3B%20because%20the%20entire%20site%20was%20enclosed.%C2%