o%20Epstein%20for%20sexualized%20massages%2C%20each%20of%20whom%20was%20paid%20%24200%20per%20session.%20One%2014-year-old%20girl%20was%20given%20%24300%20after%20giving%20Epstein%20a%20massage%20where%20he%20told%20her%20to%20strip%20naked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20memo%20dated%20that%20year%2C%20JPMorgan%20employees%20raised%20their%20eyebrows%20at%20Epstein's%20enormous%20cash%20withdrawals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCash%20withdrawals%20are%20routinely%20made%20in%20amounts%20for%20%2440%2C000%20to%20%2480%2C000%20several%20times%20a%20month%2C%20which%20total%20over%20%24750%2C000%20year%20to%20date%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23886583-jp-morgan-rapid-response-team-meeting-2006-for-jeffrey-epstein%5C%22%3Eemployees%20wrote%20in%20a%202006%20memo%20discussing%20how%20to%20handle%20him%20as%20a%20client%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20withdrawals%20rang%20alarm%20bells%2C%20Epstein%20was%20one%20of%20the%20Private%20Bank's%20most%20important%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPartly%20because%20of%20his%20connections%20to%20other%20powerful%20and%20wealthy%20people%2C%20JPMorgan's%20private%20banking%20executives%20used%20him%20as%20a%20recruiter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202003%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.nysd.591653%2Fgov.uscourts.nysd.591653.220.0.pdf%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Tuesday's%20motion%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Epstein%20was%20%26quot%3Bby%20double%2C%20the%20top%20revenue%20generator%20in%20the%20Private%20Bank.%26quot%3B%20He%20brought%20in%20clients%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fglenn-dubin-leaves-hedge-fund-distances-himself-from-epstein-reports-2020-1%5C%22%3Ebillionaire%20hedge%20fund%20manager%20Glenn%20Dubin%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Google%20cofounder%20Sergey%20Brin%2C%20and%20made%20connections%20with%20potential%20clients%20like%20Bill%20Gates%2C%20Leon%20Black%2C%20Larry%20Summers%2C%20the%20Sultan%20of%20Dubai%2C%20Prince%20Andrew%2C%20Ehud%20Barak%2C%20Thomas%20Pritzker%2C%20and%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20the%20filing%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEpstein%20died%20in%20jail%20in%202019%20while%20awaiting%20trial%20on%20sex-trafficking%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Insider%2C%20a%20JPMorgan%20representative%20said%20the%20bank%20had%20no%20knowledge%20of%20his%20sex-trafficking%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20association%20with%20Epstein%20was%20a%20mistake%20and%20in%20hindsight%20we%20regret%20it%2C%20but%20we%20did%20not%20help%20him%20commit%20his%20heinous%20crimes%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20representative%20for%20JPMorgan%20Chase%20told%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BWe%20would%20never%20have%20continued%20to%20do%20business%20with%20him%20if%20we%20believed%20he%20was%20engaged%20in%20an%20ongoing%20sex%20trafficking%20operation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EJPMorgan%20finally%20asked%20Epstein%20about%20the%20cash%20in%202011%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%20Epstein%20arrived%20at%20a%20plea%20deal%20with%20prosecutors%20in%20Florida.%20Law%20enforcement%20identified%20about%2040%20women%20and%20girls%20who%20said%20he%20sexually%20abused%20them.%20Alexander%20Acosta%2C%20a%20US%20Attorney%20at%20the%20time%2C%20came%20to%20an%20agreement%20with%20Epstein%20that%20allowed%20him%20to%20plead%20guilty%20to%20a%20couple%20of%20charges%20related%20to%20soliciting%20sex%20work%20in%20exchange%20for%20a%20quick%20stint%20in%20jail%2C%20where%20he'd%20mostly%20be%20on%20work%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJPMorgan's%20employees%20remained%20uneasy%20about%20the%20bank's%20relationship%20with%20Epstein%2C%20documents%20obtained%20by%20the%20US%20Virgin%20Islands%20show.%20But%20Epstein%20kept%20withdrawing%20enormous%20amounts%20of%20cash%2C%20despite%20the%20private%20banking%20division's%20guidelines.%20He%20continued%20to%20take%20out%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20cash%20each%20year%20from%20his%20JPMorgan%20accounts%2C%20records%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23886592-2011-rapid-response-team-jp-morgan-jeffrey-epstein%5C%22%3Ea%202011%20memo%3C%2Fa%3E%20cited%20in%20the%20148-page%20%26quot%3Bstatement%20of%20fact%26quot%3B%20document%2C%20JPMorgan%20employees%20wrote%20that%20a%20banker%20had%20another%20conversation%20with%20Epstein%20%26quot%3Bwith%20regard%20to%20large%20cash%20withdrawals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEpstein%20had%20an%20excuse%20ready.%20He%20told%20them%20he%20needed%20the%20money%20to%20pay%20for%20fuel%20when%20he%20traveled.%20JPMorgan%20made%20an%20internal%20note%20to%20reflect%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMr.%20Epstein%20withdraws%20anywhere%20from%20%2420K%20to%20%2440K%20in%20cash%20to%20pay%20for%20fuel%20expenses%20when%20he%20travels%20to%20foreign%20countries%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20memo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20page%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bstatement%20of%20fact%26quot%3B%20document%20is%20entirely%20redacted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221366%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ghislaine%20Maxwell%20Jeffrey%20Epstein%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61b10b210ee5370018455ccb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221025%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGhislaine%20Maxwell%20and%20Jeffrey%20Epstein.%3Cp%3EUS%20Attorney's%20Office%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20New%20York%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20July%2018%2C%202013%2C%20the%20continued%20cash%20withdrawals%20rang%20bells%20at%20JPMorgan's%20internal%20anti-money%20laundering%20department%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-execs-rejected-internal-request-sever-ties-with-scum-epstein-2023-7%5C%22%3Ethe%20US%20Virgin%20Islands%20described%20as%20%26quot%3BJPMorgan's%20in-house%20human%20trafficking%20experts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20compliance%20officer%20wrote%20in%20an%20email