er%20car%20in%20a%20flooded%20road%20in%20Florida.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c01809ed4f460019636ba1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFrequent%20flooding%20has%20direct%20and%20indirect%20consequences%20on%20roads%20and%20traffic%3A%20while%20some%20roads%20flood%20and%20become%20impracticable%2C%20others%20see%20traffic%20clogs%20and%20delays%20as%20drivers%20take%20alternative%20routes.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Raedle%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMore%20people%20are%20moving%20into%20disaster-prone%20areas%20than%20moving%20out%2C%20Redfin%20reported.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThat's%20as%20these%20regions%20have%20a%20larger%20housing%20inventory%20and%20an%20uptick%20in%20construction.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAlmost%20half%20of%20recently%20moved%20Americans%20think%20climate%20risks%20may%20impact%20home%20prices.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20amount%20of%20Americans%20moving%20to%20disaster-prone%20regions%20far%20outweighs%20the%20amount%20of%20people%20leaving%20them%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.redfin.com%2Fnews%2Fclimate-migration-real-estate-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERedfin%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENet%20migration%20into%20counties%20with%20flood%20risk%20was%20384%2C000%20in%202021%20and%202022%2C%20up%20103%25%20from%20the%202019-2020%20period.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20figure%20for%20areas%20at%20risk%20of%20wildfires%20was%20446%2C000%2C%20up%2051%25%2C%20and%20areas%20vulnerable%20to%20extreme%20heat%20saw%20629%2C000%20more%20people%20come%20in%20than%20leave%2C%20a%2017%25%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20human%20nature%20to%20focus%20on%20current%20benefits%2C%20like%20waterfront%20views%20or%20a%20low%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20over%20costs%20that%20could%20rack%20up%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20like%20property%20damage%20or%20a%20decrease%20in%20property%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Redfin%20Deputy%20Chief%20Economist%C2%A0Daryl%20Fairweather.%20%26quot%3BIt's%C2%A0also%20human%20nature%20to%C2%A0discount%C2%A0risks%20that%20are%20tough%20to%20measure%2C%20like%20climate%20change.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWillingness%20to%20reside%20in%20these%20areas%20is%20a%20side%20effect%20of%20the%20pandemic%20housing%20boom%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20affordability%20crisis%20that%20has%20since%20ensued%2C%20according%20to%20Redfin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20height%20of%20COVID-19%2C%20low%20mortgage%20rates%20and%20a%20burst%20of%20remote%20work%20led%20many%20homebuyers%20to%20resettle%20in%20states%20such%20as%20Florida%2C%20Texas%2C%20and%20Arizona.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20regions%20have%20ample%20housing%20availability%2C%20but%20are%20more%20exposed%20to%20dangers%20such%20as%20hurricanes%20and%20wildfires.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20do%20these%20areas%20have%20more%20inventory%20to%20choose%20from%2C%20Redfin%20found%20that%20new%20construction%20is%20also%20increasing%20in%20these%20regions.%20Over%20half%20of%20new%20homes%20built%20in%20the%20past%20decade%20are%20vulnerable%20to%20fire%20risk%2C%20while%2045%25%20are%20faced%20with%20prospects%20of%20drought.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20many%20of%20the%20new%20arrivals%20are%20aware%20of%20the%20dangers%20they%20face.%20Redfin%20surveyed%20a%20number%20of%20residents%20who%20had%20recently%20moved%20in%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20and%20found%20that%2048.7%25%20expect%20climate%20disasters%2C%20high%20temperatures%2C%20and%20rising%20sea%20levels%20to%20impact%20home%20prices%20within%20the%20next%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20perspective%20that's%20been%20previously%20pushed%20by%20DeltaTerra's%20Capital%20Dave%20Burt%20%E2%80%94%20an%20analyst%20who%20predicted%20the%202008%20housing%20crash%20%E2%80%94%20who%20cautioned%20that%20as%20much%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bu