20issued%20to%20hold%20local%20body%20polls%20after%20ensuring%20that%2033%25%20of%20the%20seats%20are%20reserved%20for%20women.%20The%20issue%20has%20become%20contentious%20in%20Nagaland%2C%20where%20political%20representation%20for%20women%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fwith-hekani-jakhalus-win-nagaland-gets-it-first-ever-woman-mla%5C%22%3Enearly%20non-existent%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-nagaland-bjp-state-governments-women-reservation-justice-kaul-233602%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Justice%20Kaul%20noted%20that%20the%20same%20political%20dispensation%20was%20in%20power%20in%20Nagaland%20and%20at%20the%20Centre.%20He%20added%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20have%20to%20be%20roped%20in%E2%80%A6.You%20are%20one%20political%20dispensation%20so%20it%20would%20be%20easier%20for%20you%20to%20actively%20participate.%20I%20refuse%20to%20let%20your%20hands%20off.%20You%20take%20extreme%20stands%20against%20other%20State%20Governments%20who%20are%20not%20amenable%20to%20you%2C%20but%20your%20own%20State%20Government%20is%20violating%20Constitutional%20provision%20and%20you%20do%20not%20want%20to%20say%20something.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202023%2C%20the%20top%20court%20had%20asked%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20place%20on%20record%20whether%20the%20constitutional%20scheme%20of%20reservation%20for%20women%20in%20local%20bodies%2C%20guaranteed%20in%20Article%20243D%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution%2C%20applies%20to%20Nagaland%20or%20if%20an%20exemption%20has%20been%20granted.%20While%20the%20government%20has%20yet%20to%20file%20an%20affidavit.%20additional%20solicitor%20general%20K.M.%20Nataraj%20orally%20submitted%20that%20he%20had%20already%20indicated%20that%20the%20constitutional%20scheme%20of%20reservation%20extends%20to%20Nagaland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20government%2C%20led%20by%20Neiphiu%20Rio%2C%20has%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F371998%2F%5C%22%3EArticle%20371A%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20which%20makes%20certain%20special%20provisions%20to%20the%20state%20%E2%80%93%20allows%20it%20to%20conduct%20local%20body%20elections%20without%20reservation%20for%20women.%20Article%20371%20holds%C2%A0that%20when%20parliament%20passes%20an%20Act%20on%20matters%20pertaining%20to%20%E2%80%9CNaga%20religious%20and%20social%20practices%3B%20Naga%20customary%20law%20and%20procedure%3B%C2%A0administration%20of%20civil%20and%20criminal%20justice%20involving%20decisions%20according%20to%20Naga%20customary%20law%3B%C2%A0ownership%20and%20transfer%20of%20land%20and%20its%20resources%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20will%20not%20apply%20shall%20apply%20to%20the%20state%20unless%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20by%20a%20resolution%20so%20decides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Raju%20said%20that%20the%20article%20does%20not%20deny%20the%20right%20of%20equality%20to%20women%20so%20far%20as%20participatory%20processes%20are%20concerned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kaul%20then%20asked%20why%20reservation%20for%20women%20was%20not%20being%20implemented%20and%20what%20the%20Union%20government%20was%20doing%20about%20it.%20%E2%80%9CPolitically%20also%20you%20are%20on%20the%20same%20page.%20It%20is%20your%20government%20in%20the%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20advocate%20general%20(AG)%20for%20Nagaland%2C%20K.N.%20Balgopal%2C%20sought%20some%20time%20from%20the%20court%20to%20%E2%80%9Cimpress%20upon%20the%20relevant%20political%20dispensation%20that%20the%20only%20way%20forward%20is%20to%20implement%20the%20mandate%20of%20having%20one-third%20reservation%20in%20the%20municipalities%E2%80%9D%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Justice%20Kaul%20noted%20that%20such%20a%20request%20has%20been%20made%20by%20the%20AG%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnth%20time%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20granted%20him%20%E2%80%9Cone%20last%20of%20the%20last%20opportunity%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENagaland%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-nagaland-local-polls-women-quota%5C%22%3Eheld%20only%3C%2Fa%3E%20one%20local%20body%20election%20so%20far%2C%20in%202004%2C%20which%20did%20not%20comply%20with%20the%20mandate%20for%201%2F3rd%20reservation%20for%20women.%20An%20attempt%20to%20hold%20the%20elections%20in%202017%2C%20with%20women%E2%80%99s%20reservations%2C%20had%20to%20be%20called%20off%20due%20to%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Rio%20government%20wanted%20to%20hold%20elections%20in%20May%20this%20year%20without%20the%20quota%20for%20women%2C%20the%20top%20court%20stayed%20the%20order.%20The%20government%20then%20said%20it%20would%20hold%20the%20elections%20with%20the%20constitutionally%20mandated%20reservation%2C%20but%20then%20asked%20the%20State%20Election%20Commission%20to%20cancel%20them.%20Rio%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-nagaland-women-reservation-contempt-neiphiu-rio%5C%22%3Ereceived%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20contempt%20notice%20from%20the%20top%20court%20for%20not%20honouring%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Law%20before%20social%20change%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kaul%20said%20during%20the%20hearing%20that%20reservation%20ensures%20that%20a%20minimal%20level%20of%20representation%20for%20all%20sections%20of%20society.%20%E2%80%9CReservation%20is%20a%20concept%20of%20affirmative%20action.%20Women%20reservation%20is%20based%20on%20that.%20How%20do%20you%20get%20out%20of%20the%20constitutional%20provision%3F%20I%20do%20not%20understand%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAG%20Balgopal%20said%20that%C2%A0calls%20to%20boycott%20local%20body%20elections%2C%20if%20held%20with%20the%20quota%20for%20women%2C%20by%20a%20majority%20of%20tribal%20bodies%20was%20an%20%E2%80%9Cimpediment%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20present%20government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cintention%20to%20hold%20elections%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Justice%20Kaul%20said%20that%20these%20organisations%20have%20the%20right%20not%20to%20participate%20in%20elections%20but%20that%20should%20not%20prevent%20the%20state%20government%20from%20implementing%20the%20mandate%20of%20the%20constitution.%20He%20asked%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20%5Bis%20there%5D%20resistance%20to%20participation%20of%20women%20when%20in%20all%20walks%20of%20life%2C%20women%20are%20equally%20involved%3F%20Why%20do%20you%20hesitate%20in%20giving%20even%20one-third%20representation%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%2C%20Balgopal%20said%20that%20he%20had%20%E2%80%9Cpersonally%20met%E2%80%9D%20some%20women%E2%80%99s%20organisations%20in%20Nagaland%2C%20and%20that%20the%20members%20of%20one%20major%20organisation%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthey%20do%20not%20want%20reservation%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kaul%20rejected%20this%2C%20saying%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20a%20social%20progression%20takes%20place%20it%20is%20the%20law%20often%20that%20comes%20first%20and%20that%20often%20becomes%20an%20impetus%20for%20social%20change.%20If%20anything%20was%20left%20to%20be%20done%20voluntarily%20many%20things%20would%20not%20have%20happened%20after%201950.%20Do%20you%20think%20men%20under%20Hindu%20law%20would%20have%20agreed%20to%20have%20only%20one%20wife%3F%20The%20rights%20of%20women%20in%20estate%20and%20property%20would%20have%20arisen%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20always%20resistance%20to%20change%20of%20status%20quo.%20But%2C%20someone%20has%20to%20take%20initiative%20to%20change%20the%20status%20quo%20for%20the%20better.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690304