0absence%20from%20the%20public%20eye.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20was%20forced%20to%20comment%20on%20Qin%20not%20travelling%20to%20Indonesia%20to%20attend%20the%20ASEAN%20and%20East%20Asia%20ministerial%20meetings.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20China%20had%20claimed%20that%20he%20had%20%E2%80%9Chealth%20reasons%E2%80%9D.%20Incidentally%2C%20the%20line%20was%20later%20taken%20out%20from%20the%20official%20transcript%20of%20the%20briefing.%20Qin%20also%20didn%E2%80%99t%20travel%20to%20the%20BRICS%20foreign%20ministers%E2%80%99%20meeting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20Qin%20not%20in%20the%20picture%2C%20Wang%20had%20stepped%20in%2C%20travelling%20to%20all%20the%20major%20international%20meetings%20over%20the%20last%20month.%20Qin%E2%80%99s%20absence%20had%20led%20to%20some%20of%20his%20counterparts%20from%20other%20countries%20to%20postpone%20their%20visits%20to%20Beijing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20foreign%20minister%2C%20Qin%E2%80%99s%20first%20foreign%20foray%20had%20been%20to%20New%20Delhi%20to%20attend%20the%20G-20%20foreign%20ministers%20meeting%20in%20March.%20He%20had%20also%20come%20to%20India%20for%20the%20SCO%20foreign%20ministers%20meeting%20in%20Goa.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWang%20is%20currently%20in%20Johannesburg%20to%20attend%20the%20meeting%20of%20the%20National%20Security%20Advisors%20of%20the%20BRICS%20summit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKnown%20to%20have%20been%20close%20to%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20there%20had%20been%20feverish%20speculation%20about%20the%20reason%20for%20Qin%E2%80%99s%20appearance%2C%20since%20he%20took%20over%20the%20post%20only%20this%20year.%20His%20career%20trajectory%20had%20been%20smooth%20till%20now%2C%20having%20been%20a%20foreign%20ministry%20spokesperson%20and%20appointed%20as%20the%20Chinese%20ambassador%20to%20the%20United%20States%20in%202021.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20weeks%2C%20questions%20were%20repeatedly%20raised%20at%20the%20daily%20briefings%20of%20the%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20about%20Qin.%20However%2C%20the%20only%20answer%20was%20they%20had%20no%20information%20to%20share.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20one%20of%20the%20speculation%20online%20being%20that%20Qin%20was%20sidelined%20over%20an%20alleged%20extramarital%20affair%2C%20the%20question%20was%20even%20raised%20during%20the%20media%20briefing.%20But%2C%20as%20usual%2C%20the%20foreign%20ministry%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20she%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20information.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-china-66125055%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBBC%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20there%20had%20been%20a%205%2C000%25%20surge%20in%20searches%20for%20Qin%20in%20China%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20search%20engine%2C%20Baidu%2C%20in%20a%20week.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20not%20uncommon%20for%20high-profile%20Chinese%20personalities%20to%20%E2%80%98disappear%E2%80%99%20for%20some%20time%2C%20presumably%20because%20they%20annoyed%20the%20establishment.%20This%20included%20industrialist%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-china-65084344%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EJack%20Ma%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20top%20tennis%20player%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fwhere-is-peng-shuai%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPeng%20Shuai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20However%2C%20Qin%20is%20certainly%20one%20of%20the%20highest-ranking%20officials%20to%20have%20been%20removed%20from%20the%20public%20sphere%20in%20recent%20times.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20eminent%20China%20watcher%2C%20MIT%E2%80%99s%20M.%20Taylor%20Fraver%2C%20Wang%20Yi%20will%20now%20be%20the%20first%20foreign%20minister%20in%20more%20than%20two%20decades%20(since%20Qian%20Qichen)%20to%20be%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Politburo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EWang%20Yi%20will%20now%20be%20the%20first%20foreign%20minister%20in%20two%20plus%20decades%20(since%20Qian%20Qichen)%20to%20be%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Politburo%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20M.%20Taylor%20Fravel%20(%40fravel)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Ffravel%2Fstatus%2F1683814911778910209%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%2025%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDennis%20Wilder%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20Asian%20studies%20at%20Georgetown%20University%2C%20said%20that%20Wang%20Yi%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Csafest%20choice%20possible%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EWang%20Yi%20is%20the%20safest%20choice%20possible.%20Well%20known%20around%20the%20world%20he%20will%20project%20continuity%20in%20Chinese%20foreign%20policy.%20Xi%20needs%20to%20reassure%20the%20globe%20that%20there%20is%20no%20deep%20problem%20in%20the%20Chinese%20leadership.%20That%20Qin%20Gang%E2%80%99s%20problems%20are%20personal%20not%20national.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FTsuYo6ohct%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FTsuYo6ohct%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Dennis%20Wilder%E5%81%89%E5%BE%B7%E5%AF%A7%20(%40dennisw5)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fdennisw5%2Fstatus%2F1683803027713449987%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%2025%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20is%20Qin%20Gang%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQin%20was%20one%20of%20the%20earliest%20Chinese%20diplomats%20to%20make%20sharp%20comments%20in%20defence%20of%20Beijing%E2%80%99s%20increasingly%20assertive%20foreign%20policy%20positions.%20Those%20remarks%20earned%20him%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fis-china-pivoting-away-from-wolf-warrior-diplomacy%2Fa-64435396%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fis-china-pivoting-away-from-wolf-warrior-diplomacy%2Fa-64435396%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3Ereputation%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cwolf%20warrior%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20nickname%20given%20to%20Chinese%20diplomats%20who%20respond%20vehemently%20to%20Western%20nations%20they%20perceive%20as%20hostile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20he%20complained%20that%20China%E2%80%99s%20global%20image%20had%20worsened%20because%20Western%20media%20had%20never%20accepted%20the%20Chinese%20political%20system%20or%20its%20economic%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQin%20rapidly%20rose%20within%20the%20Communist%20Party%20hierarchy%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20say%20the%20rise%20was%20due%20to%20his%20closeness%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fxi-jinping%2Ft-17449321%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fxi-jinping%2Ft-17449321%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3EPresident%20Xi%20Jinping.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%202014%20to%202017%2C%20Qin%20worked%20as%20head%20of%20the%20foreign%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20diplomatic%20protocol%20department.%20During%20this%20stint%2C%20he%20had%20regular%20contact%20with%20Xi%20and%20organized%20the%20president%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20trips.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQin%20was%20viewed%20as%20Xi%E2%80%99s%20prot%C3%A9g%C3%A9%20and%20appointed%20as%20a%20vice-minister%20of%20foreign%20affairs%2C%20a%20role%20he%20held%20between%202018%20and%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfterward%2C%20he%20was%20sent%20to%20Washington%20as%20China%E2%80%99s%20ambassador%20to%20the%20United%20States%2C%20where%20he%20gained%20prominence%20through%20public%20and%20media%20appearances%20in%20which%20he%20stridently%20defended%20Chinese%20geopolitical%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20as%20ambassador%2C%20he%20was%20less%20confrontational%20than%20he%20had%20been%20previously%20in%20Beijing.%20In%20that%20role%2C%20he%20was%20charged%20with%20putting%20the%20relationship%20between%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20two%20largest%20economies%20back%20on%20track.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fwho-is-qin-gang-chinas-sacked-foreign-minister%2Fa-66345677%5C%22%3EInputs%20from%20DW%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20used%20in%20this%20article)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20Additional%20information%20was%20added%20to%20this%20article%20after%20it%20was%20published.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690289446000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25181139%2FQin_Gang_and_Wang_Yi_2023.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fchina-qin-gang-replaced-foreign-minister-disappear%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CQin%20Gang%20was%20removed%20from%20the%20position%20of%20Minister%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%3B%20Appoint%20Wang%20Yi%20as%20foreign%20minister%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20terse%20news%20flash%20issued%20by%20the%20state%20media%20agency%20Xinhua.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fchina-qin-gang-replaced-foreign-minister-disappear%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Estonia%20sinking%3A%20Ramp%20from%20ferry%20wreck%20raised%20after%2029%20years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690288945000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FFF64%2Fproduction%2F_130508356_4d966cb0c27c1faf6598936c95286dcc582803a60_46_6000_33751000x563.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fww