20written%20reply%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20home%20affairs%20Nityanand%20Rai%20rejected%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20estimates%20by%20providing%20data%20from%20a%20Report%20of%20the%20Technical%20Group%20on%20Population%20Projections%20published%20by%20the%20National%20Commission%20on%20Population%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20%26amp%3B%20Family%20Welfare.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20per%20United%20Nations%2C%20Department%20of%20Economic%20and%20Social%20Affairs%2C%20Population%20Division%20online%20publication%2C%20World%20Population%20Prospectus%202022%2C%20the%20total%20projected%20population%20of%20China%20as%20on%201st%20July%2C%202023%20is%20142%2C56%2C71%2C000%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Rai.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20projected%20population%20of%20India%20as%20on%201st%20July%2C%202023%2C%20as%20per%20Report%20of%20the%20Technical%20Group%20on%20Population%20Projections%20published%20by%20National%20Commission%20on%20Population%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20%26amp%3B%20Family%20Welfare%2C%20is%20139%2C23%2C29%2C000.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20April%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fdevelopment%2Fdesa%2Fdpad%2Fpublication%2Fun-desa-policy-brief-no-153-india-overtakes-china-as-the-worlds-most-populous-country%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20United%20Nations%20Department%20of%20Economic%20and%20Social%20Affairs%20(UN%20DESA)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20latest%20estimates%20and%20projections%20of%20global%20population%20from%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20indicate%20that%20China%20will%20soon%20cede%20its%20long-held%20status%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20populous%20country.%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20April%202023%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%20is%20expected%20to%20reach%201%2C425%2C775%2C850%20people%2C%20matching%20and%20then%20surpassing%20the%20population%20of%20mainland%20China.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20did%20not%20however%20state%20the%20exact%20date%20on%20which%20India%20would%20have%20surpassed%20China%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%20saying%20only%20that%20it%20would%20happen%20sometime%20in%20mid-2023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20stated%20that%20while%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%20is%20virtually%20certain%20to%20continue%20to%20grow%20for%20several%20decades%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20population%20reached%20its%20peak%20size%20recently%20and%20experienced%20a%20decline%20during%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20added%20that%20projections%20indicate%20that%20the%20size%20of%20the%20Chinese%20population%20will%20continue%20to%20fall%20and%20could%20drop%20below%201%20billion%20before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20century.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20noted%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20growth%20was%20harder%20to%20estimate%20because%20a%20population%20census%20has%20not%20be%20conducted%20since%202011.%20The%202021%20census%20was%20delayed%20because%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20and%20will%20likely%20be%20conducted%20in%202024.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20in%20his%20reply%20to%20parliament%2C%20Rai%20did%20not%20provide%20a%20specific%20answer%20as%20to%20when%20the%20next%20census%20could%20be%20conducted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20intent%20of%20the%20Government%20for%20conducting%20Census%202021%20was%20notified%20in%20Gazette%20of%20India%20on%2028th%20March%2C%202019.%20Due%20to%20outbreak%20of%20COVID19%20pandemic%2C%20the%20Census%202021%20and%20the%20related%20field%20activities%20have%20been%20postponed%20(sic)%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20India%E2%80%99s%20young%20population%2C%20which%20continues%20to%20grow%2C%20offers%20an%20opportunity%20for%20India%20to%20reap%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eso-called%20demographic%20dividend%2C%20concerns%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehave%20also%20been%20raised%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findia-overtaking-china-in-population%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20shortcomings%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eeducation%20and%20healthcare%20infrastructure.%20But%20experts%20have%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsociety%2Findia-china-highest-populated%5C%22%3Epointed%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20concerns%20about%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpopulation%20explosion%E2%80%9D%20are%20unwarranted%20because%20several%20states%20in%20the%20country%20have%20already%20achieved%20%E2%80%98replacement%20level%E2%80%99%20total%20fertility%20rate%20%E2%80%93%20whereby%20the%20population%20remains%20stable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690284932000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25170231%2F3107780632_e1447cc651_h.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findia-projected-population-july-1-behind-china-govt-lok-sabha%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20April%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20said%20that%20its%20latest%20estimates%20and%20projections%20of%20global%20population%20show%20that%20China%20%26quot%3Bwill%20soon%20cede%20its%20long-held%20status%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20populous%20country%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findia-projected-population-july-1-behind-china-govt-lok-sabha%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2220%20cuts%20for%20Akshay%20starrer%20%E2%80%98OMG%202%E2%80%99%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690283839000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102108752%2Cimgsize-65534.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https